reviews.review_text: This is my favourite McDonalds, I always go there around the same time but it has never been busy when I went in there. I always get just a 6 piece nuggets and idk what they do- maybe overcook them a little but I swear to god they are the best nuggets you will ever have in a McDonalds in Vancouver! No sauce required, they are that good. Also the employees are very nice and corteous. One of them even charged my phone for me (which definitely is not in their job description). Kid-friendliness: Happy meals are affordable

Used the drive through most times, once in a while I stopped in for dining in when I used to work around the area. Its an express location so it has only three dining tables. Kid-friendliness: Kids menu available Wheelchair accessibility: The wheelchair accessible entrance is in front and has a very small dining area may cause a problem if you want to use your wheelchair. But if you are doing take out lots of space to use your wheelchair.
Mcdonalds.  Classic food, great taste. No issues with this location - drive thru is fast and efficient (been here numerous times in the past) but usually out of my way to frequent too often Food

Wow! The staff here are great. They seem to get along well too. I go there every Saturday morning and the drive through person who took my order even remembered my order from before! My breakfast burrito with apple juice. Hahaha. 5 stars.
